      <guid>//crypt0.net/daily/daily-trust-news-2017-04-20/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Daily Security news from &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/trustpath&#34;&gt;@trustpath&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Two local accounting firms say over 8000 clients hit by data breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Greater Boston firms have alerted the state that clients&amp;rsquo; personal information, including Social Security numbers, may have been exposed in data &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/news/2017/04/19/two-local-accounting-firms-say-over-8-000-clients.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/news/2017/04/19/two-local-accounting-firms-say-over-8-000-clients.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Cylance Protect endpoint protection system interfering with Laserfiche or&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Has anyone had trouble with Cylance Protect endpoint protection system interfering with Laserfiche or Quick Fields? We&amp;rsquo;re experiencing some very &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://answers.laserfiche.com/questions/119544/Cylance-Protect-endpoint-protection-system-interfering-with-Laserfiche-or-Quick-Fields&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://answers.laserfiche.com/questions/119544/Cylance-Protect-endpoint-protection-system-interfering-with-Laserfiche-or-Quick-Fields&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;What is a mandatory data breach notification?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not all data breaches will require notifications. In order to trigger the notification requirement a reasonable person would need to conclude that there &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.mondaq.com/australia/x/587178/data+protection/What+is+a+mandatory+data+breach+notification&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.mondaq.com/australia/x/587178/data+protection/What+is+a+mandatory+data+breach+notification&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Mount Pleasant restaurant Another Broken Egg Cafe says hackers may have&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charleston Post Courier The state Consumer Affairs agency says that at least 67,000 South Carolinians were affected by data breaches in shops and food service locations &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.postandcourier.com/business/mount-pleasant-restaurant-another-broken-egg-cafe-says-hackers-may/article_a0386aa8-251f-11e7-bad9-b31fcb91b695.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.postandcourier.com/business/mount-pleasant-restaurant-another-broken-egg-cafe-says-hackers-may/article_a0386aa8-251f-11e7-bad9-b31fcb91b695.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Get ready for mandatory reporting of data breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On 22 February this year the Privacy Amendment (Notifiable Data Breaches) Act 2017 received Royal Assent and on 22 February 2018 the new &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.australiandefence.com.au/news/get-ready-for-mandatory-reporting-of-data-breaches&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.australiandefence.com.au/news/get-ready-for-mandatory-reporting-of-data-breaches&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Irish companies still unprepared for data breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More than 40 per cent of Irish organisations do not have plans in place to deal with possible data breaches, while 13 per cent don&amp;rsquo;t even know where &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.irishtimes.com/business/technology/irish-companies-still-unprepared-for-data-breaches-1.3052890&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.irishtimes.com/business/technology/irish-companies-still-unprepared-for-data-breaches-1.3052890&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Unfixed Issues in Symantec Endpoint Protection 14.0.2349.0100&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;copy right page it is still showing 1991-2016 only it is suppose to be &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.symantec.com/connect/ideas/unfixed-issues-symantec-endpoint-protection-14023490100&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.symantec.com/connect/ideas/unfixed-issues-symantec-endpoint-protection-14023490100&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Smashing Security #017: Data breaches, zero day exploits, and toenail&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Graham Cluley Security News Hotel malware has been stealing guests&amp;rsquo; payment card details&amp;hellip; again, should businesses relay delay rolling out vulnerability patches, and Burger &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.grahamcluley.com/smashing-security-017-data-breaches-zero-day-exploits-and-toenail-clippings/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.grahamcluley.com/smashing-security-017-data-breaches-zero-day-exploits-and-toenail-clippings/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Cyber security topic of national summit in Oklahoma City&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the summit, a series of workshops were held about data breaches and cybersecurity involving law firms, financial businesses, the gaming &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://newsok.com/cyber-security-topic-of-national-summit-in-oklahoma-city/article/5546127&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://newsok.com/cyber-security-topic-of-national-summit-in-oklahoma-city/article/5546127&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;42% of Irish businesses have no plan to handle data breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Companies that suffer data breaches and are found to be non-compliant with the regulation will be liable to fines of up to 20 million or 4% of global &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://irishtechnews.ie/42-of-irish-businesses-have-no-plan-to-handle-data-breaches/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://irishtechnews.ie/42-of-irish-businesses-have-no-plan-to-handle-data-breaches/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;ServiceNow Survey Finds Over 80% of CISOs Say Data Breaches That They Know&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yahoo Finance CISOs are spending an increasing amount on preventing and detecting data breaches, but our research underscores that response is where they &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://finance.yahoo.com/news/servicenow-survey-finds-over-80-120000883.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://finance.yahoo.com/news/servicenow-survey-finds-over-80-120000883.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Data Breaches on Track to Reach 1500 in 2017&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The latest count from the Identity Theft Resource Center (ITRC) indicates there have been 456 data breaches recorded this year through April 18 and &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://247wallst.com/technology-3/2017/04/20/data-breaches-on-track-to-reach-1500-in-2017/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://247wallst.com/technology-3/2017/04/20/data-breaches-on-track-to-reach-1500-in-2017/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;VDI can help improve hospitals&amp;rsquo; IT security and rein in costs  Here&amp;rsquo;s how&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Providers&amp;rsquo; increased use of mobile and cloud technology in care has unintentionally contributed to the recent rise in data breaches. The greater &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.beckershospitalreview.com/healthcare-information-technology/vdi-can-help-improve-hospitals-it-security-and-rein-in-costs-here-s-how.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.beckershospitalreview.com/healthcare-information-technology/vdi-can-help-improve-hospitals-it-security-and-rein-in-costs-here-s-how.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Cost of cybersecurity breaches more than just financial, says expert&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kemp said that the new General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) will require businesses to be more open about the major data breaches they &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.out-law.com/en/articles/2017/april/cost-of-cybersecurity-breaches-more-than-just-financial-says-expert-/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.out-law.com/en/articles/2017/april/cost-of-cybersecurity-breaches-more-than-just-financial-says-expert-/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;ServiceNow Survey Finds Over 80% of CISOs Say Data Breaches That They Know&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Wire (press release) ServiceNow and Oxford Economics surveyed 300 Chief Information Security Officers around the world to identify how leaders are responding to &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170420005261/en/ServiceNow-Survey-Finds-80-CISOs-Data-Breaches&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170420005261/en/ServiceNow-Survey-Finds-80-CISOs-Data-Breaches&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Wonga and GameStop Investigate Potential Data Breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is impossible to deny the threat posed by data breaches. Whether it is consumer information or payment details getting exposed, companies are &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://themerkle.com/wonga-and-gamestop-investigate-potential-data-breaches/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://themerkle.com/wonga-and-gamestop-investigate-potential-data-breaches/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;CISOs Admit They Are Unable to Keep Pace with Data Breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the most part, cybersecurity seems to continue to be reactive rather than proactive. Yes, security systems are in place to prevent potential incidents, &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.itbusinessedge.com/blogs/data-security/cisos-admit-they-are-unable-to-keep-pace-with-data-breaches.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.itbusinessedge.com/blogs/data-security/cisos-admit-they-are-unable-to-keep-pace-with-data-breaches.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Amid data concerns, transparency can pay off&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After data breaches at several major hotel companies, including one most recently at IHG that reportedly affected more than 1,100 properties, hotels &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.hotelsmag.com/Industry/News/Details/72808&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.hotelsmag.com/Industry/News/Details/72808&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Thales: 54% of Japanese enterprises increase IT security spending&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Despite this year&amp;rsquo;s numbers, only 44% of respondents believe that compliance is &amp;lsquo;very&amp;rsquo; or &amp;lsquo;extremely&amp;rsquo; effective at preventing data breaches.  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cambridgenetwork.co.uk/news/thales-54pc-japanese-enterprises-increase-it-security/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.cambridgenetwork.co.uk/news/thales-54pc-japanese-enterprises-increase-it-security/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Credentials Under Attack, Time to Exploit Still a Problem, Study Finds&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using credentials to attempt to breach networks and systems is a fundamental activity of online attackers. Since 2011, the use of stolen credentials &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.eweek.com/security/credentials-under-attack-time-to-exploit-still-a-problem-study-finds&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.eweek.com/security/credentials-under-attack-time-to-exploit-still-a-problem-study-finds&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
